column3: Text
Hey there!
Hi! What'cha doing?
Watering the cactuses.
Don't you mean cacti?
No! That's a common misconception, actually. Both cacti and cactuses are correct. I just prefer cactuses because it sounds funny.
Huh. That's interesting.
Hey. Wanna know a cactus fact?
Definitely.

Water marks can cause discoloration on cactuses. Specifically hard water, that is. That's why it's important to water cactuses from the bottom. Also, did you know cactus juice has a variety of health benefits? The juice from a prickly pear cactus can actually help ease symptoms of arthritis.
Really?
Yeah, but these cactuses don't produce any juice sadly. So, what about you? You're new here, huh? What are you up to?
I'm trying to find someone to give my million-dollar inheritance to.
Really?
No.
Well, thank goodness. I was worried for a second.
Really?
No.
Aww. I would've liked some money myself.
What do you think about [REDACTED]?
He's a great guy. You know? One of those people you just couldn't live without.
Why, the other day, he came by and gave me this drawing. It was so pretty I just had to hang it up. It's there in the house. Check it out!
So. What do you think?
Wow. I'd like one of those myself. Does he do commissions?
I don't know, but probably! I mean, there's not much to do out here, haha.
That's great! I'll ask him about it. Do you know where I could find him?
That's great! I'll ask him about it. Do you know where I could find him?
I think he's usually in that building with those swirls on it. You can't miss... Oh! I shouldn't have told you that. Rosetta will kill me. Just keep mum about it, won't you?
I will.
Thank you. Thank you. I'm sure that's the best course of action. After all, it's just a commission right?
Right.

It's no big deal... Oh, what if she finds out anyway? Please don't tell anyone! I don't want to turn up like Joe, you know. He was so torn up about it when he - Oh god! I've done it again! I'm so sorry. I don't know what's wrong with me. You better go.
Don't worry. No one will know. Take care Louis.
